d: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, good deeds bring brightness upon the face, a light in the heart, an expanse of provision, strength in the body, and love in the hearts of the creation. And evil deeds bring blackness upon the face, darkness\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21143,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/11\/07\/keep-helping-the-poor\/","url_meta":{"origin":26898,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Rizq: You are given provision for helping the weak","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 7, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: There were two brothers in the time of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, one of whom would attend the lessons of the Prophet and the other would engage in business. The businessman complained to the Prophet about his brother, and the Prophet said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26680,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/06\/28\/malik-personality-easiest-deeds\/","url_meta":{"origin":26898,"position":2},"title":"Malik on Personality: Everyone do good deeds easiest for them","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 28, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abdul Barr reported: Abdullah ibn Abdul Aziz wrote to Malik, may Allah have mercy on him, encouraging him to isolate himself for worship and discouraging him from gatherings of knowledge. Malik wrote back to him, \u201cAllah Almighty has distributed good deeds just as he has distributed provision. A man\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35278,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/20\/four-leftover-jahiliyyah\/","url_meta":{"origin":26898,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Jahiliyyah: Four traits remain from pre-Islamic ignorance","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 20, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Malik al-Ash\u2019ari reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cFour traits in my nation are among the affairs of ignorance that they have not abandoned: boasting over status, disparaging over lineage, seeking rain by the stars, and wailing over the dead.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 934 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19028,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/05\/07\/only-supported-help-weak\/","url_meta":{"origin":26898,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Welfare: Muslims only supported if helping the weak","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 7, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cSeek out your vulnerable on my behalf. Verily, you are only given provision and support from Allah due to the weak among you.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1702 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0651\u064e\u0631\u0652\u062f\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11864,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/29\/speechh-haqq-silence-safe\/","url_meta":{"origin":26898,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Silence: Speak truth, or be silent and safe","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 29, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cMay Allah have mercy on a man who spoke rightly and was rewarded, or who was silent and remained safe.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n 4589 Grade:\u00a0Hasan\u00a0(fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/26898","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/